      "name": "Monte Carlo UQ — 95th-percentile NIH envelope validation",
      "description": "Five-hundred Latin hypercube samples spanning viscosity, pump rotational speed tolerance (±1%), and inlet flow rate uncertainty (±0.2 L/min) are propagated through the CFD surrogate. The 95th-percentile NIH across all samples and all five operating conditions is 0.0078 g/100 L, remaining below the 0.01 g/100 L clinical threshold with a margin of 22%. Convergence of the Monte Carlo estimator is confirmed by halving-interval bootstrap (relative standard error < 2%).",
      "prov:wasDerivedFrom": "https://uofa.net/synth/data/monte-carlo-uq-outputs",
      "outcome": "Pass",
      "metricValue": 0.0078,
